I am currently an Engineering Manager at the Democratic National Committee.

I'm a software engineer (and teacher always). I love building and managing great teams, and I like to have a role in building tech that makes people's lives easier, better, and/or more fun. I enjoy being part of teams who learn from each other, try new things, and ship.

I've worked in research labs, startups, and in civic technology, but in my "past life" I was a lecturer and researched computing education, and am happy to share more about that work.

I used to use Twitter, but not lately; you can find me on Mastodon at jczetta@vis.social occasionally. My personal GitHub is separate from my work GitHub so it's pretty sparse these days -- when I'm not working, I'm often bookbinding, working with film (photography), biking, or something involving food.

You can find more about me at the surrounding links, or reach out: jczetta at gmail.
